RACE.FOOTNOTES: LITTLE SISTER SUE chased the pace between rivals and while two wide, then bid gamely on the turn to edge past the pace setter mid stretch then drew off driving to prevail in the end. SWEET SASSY PANTS broke outwardly and bumped rival then vied for the lead while two wide, inched away headed into the turn to lead the way into the early stretch then was over taken by an outside rival in late stretch and was best for second place. LEAFLET settled along the inside early, then came out four wide on the turn to rally in the stretch and closed well for show. MISS QUEST vied for the lead from the inside, then gave way to the outer rival into the turn then continued to flatten out in the stretch. LADY ARAMINTA was bumped at the start, then moved up while two wide to rally along the inside on the turn but came up evenly in the stretch. SUPER CHRISTIE hesitated slightly at the start, then chased the pace along the inside, bid from the two path on the turn then gave way in the stretch. MALIBU ANNA chased the pace in the middle of the pack while three wide, then made a mild bid on the turn before flattening out in the last furlongs. C C REVENGE settled towards the back of the field then continued to lose ground throughout and was no factor.
